ities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Petecio faces China's Xu Zichun in the quarterfinals on Sunday, August 4, for a guaranteed medal.\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 1037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 954, \"end\": 959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.963119566089333, \"rank\": 0.026198578090071572, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Narrowly losing an opening round devoid of action, Petecio gained a sense of urgency as she picked up the pace in the second round, landing a well-timed right hook that nearly sent Zidani to the canvas.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although the referee refused to give Zidani the count, Petecio won the second round convincingly to turn the tides on the reigning European Games champion.\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1374, \"end\": 1388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Games\", \"score\": 0.9310588711540388, \"rank\": 0.06583449212532738, \"text\": \"European Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Petecio remained the aggressor in the third round and did just enough to clinch the victory as she stayed in the hunt of repeating as an Olympic medalist.\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1554, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Believing she won, Zidani's jaw dropped when Petecio's name was announced the winner, much to the dismay of the partisan French crowd.\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With Petecio through, all of the three remaining Filipino boxers are a win away from at least a bronze.\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1795, \"entities\"